efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(L) where L is the length of the longest string
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The algorithm iteratively compares the last characters of the three strings. If they are not equal, it deletes the last character of the mismatching string and increments the operation count. This process continues until all three strings become equal or one of them becomes empty. The time complexity is linear with respect to the length of the longest string as each character is processed at most once. The space complexity is constant as the algorithm uses a fixed amount of extra space regardless of the input size.

